  "title": "Add Ship.js as a release tool",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Purpose**\r\n- A unified tool over all the InstantSearch repositories\r\n- Less chore & less mistakes\r\n\r\n**Description**\r\nI've forked this repository and put changes there to simulate how it will look like on this repository.\r\n\r\n1. Not to ruin anything accidentally, I've change the package name: https://github.com/eunjae-lee/instantsearch.js/commit/c5dd2d3069c6d5ae9caf133860e8137baed03a19\r\n2. This commit adds Ship.js to the repository.  I've left comments to the commit: https://github.com/eunjae-lee/instantsearch.js/commit/2efc50e381f54f73dcb8d4cf963a635891cb3705\r\n3. After that, I ran `yarn release:prepare` and it created this PR: https://github.com/eunjae-lee/instantsearch.js/pull/1\r\n4. Assuming this repository is configured on CircleCI, merging the PR will trigger `yarn release:trigger` and it will publish it to NPM.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisite**\r\nBranching strategy still needs to be discussed.\r\nCurrently, InstantSearch.js uses `develop` and `master`.\r\nThe description above assumes we keep the strategy.\r\nIf we decide to change it to have only `master`, I will update this issue.\r\n\r\nPlease leave your feedback or any concern.",
